.TH ilper 1  1-Mar-2012 "PILBox peripherials emulation" ""
.SH NAME
ilper \- Mass storage and Video emulation for the PILBox
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ilper
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ilper
(1) is an peripherials emulator for usage with the PILBox. The PILBox is
a USB/HP-IL converter to use with HP-IL controller, as the HP-41C*, HP-75C
and HP71B. The PILBox is designed and build by Jean-Francois Garnier.
.PP
It emulates a video display at address 1 and a Mass storage at address 2.
.PP
A scope mode is available to "capture" and "print" all HP-IL frames.
.PP
When launched,
.B ilper
(1) will show 3 windows as follow:
.nf
+-------------------------------[ ILPER 1.35.1 ]--------------------------------+
|                                                                               |
| +-< Mass Storage LIF File >---------+   +-< PILBox Link >-------+             |
| |LIF:HDRIVE1.DAT                    |   |Device:/dev/ttyUSB0    |     [STOP ] |
| +-----------------------------------+   +-----------------------+             |
|                                                                               |
+-< Display >---------------------------+-< Scope:scope.out >-------------------+
|                                       | IFC      AAU      AAD 01   TAD 01     |
|T=  0.0000                             | SAI      DAB 2E   UNL      LAD 01     |
|Z=  0.0000                             | UNL      AAU      AAD 01   TAD 01     |
|Y=  0.0000                             | SAI      DAB 2E   LAD 01   UNL        |
|X=  0.0000                             | AAU      AAD 01   TAD 01   SAI        |
|                                       | DAB 2E   LAD 01   DAB 0D   DAB 0A     |
.fi
.PP
The top window contains three fields:
.TP
\(bu \fB< Mass Storage LIF File >\fP
.br
show the current LIF image used,
.TP
\(bu \fB< PILBox Link >\fP
.br
show the current device where the PILBox is connected,
.TP
\(bu \fB[START]\fP \fB[STOP ]\fP
.br
the state of emulation STARTed or STOPped.
.sp
The reverse video field is the active one. To select another field, use the TAB
key.
.br
To change the value of value of LIF or Device, press ENTER, enter the new value and
press ENTER to set.
.br
To START or STOP, just press ENTER as a flip-flop.
.PP
The left bottom window is the display area. It works as a printer or a video
device. If \fB< Display:display.out >\fP is shown, all the text printed in
this window will be also written in the file
.I display.out
located in the current directory.
.PP
The right bottom window is the scope window and it prints the all the frames
seen on the HP-IL. If \fB< Scope:scope.out >\fP is shown, all the frames
printed in this window will be also written in the file
.I scope.out
located in the current directory.
.PP
The following commands are accepted:
.IP
.nf
  h - Display a help
  v - Display the software version
  a - Start the emulation
  o - Stop the emulation
  l - Change the LIF File
  p - Change the device for the PILBox Link
  s - Enable/Disable the HP-IL scope mode
  S - Enable/Disable the HP-IL scope recording into the file scope.out
  D - Enable/Disable the HP-IL display recording into the file display.out
  q or Q - Close teh PILBox and exit
.fi
.PP
To exit from
.B ilper
(1), just press Q or q.
.SH FILES
.I /dev/ttyUSBx
.br
.I display.out
.br
.I scope.out
.SH REFERENCES
.I http://www.jeffcalc.hp41.eu/hpil/index.html
The HP-IL resource page and the PILBox from Jean-Francois Garnier.
.sp
.I http://www.hpmuseum.net/exhibit.php?catdoc=9
The HP-IL system - Gerry Kane, Steve Harper and David Ushijima.
.sp
