The reference site containing an extensive HP-IL documentation.
.SH NOTES
The PILBox needs the FTDI driver to be installed inside Linux or *Nix host.
Recent Linux versions provide the driver as module to be dynamically loaded
before to connect the PILBox. Also, moderns Linux distributions have tools
to detect and insert the good module automatically when the PILBox is plugged.
.PP
The HP82160A HP-IL module is mandatory to use the PILBox with the HP-41C*.
.SH BUGS
The PILBox 115200 bauds optimization is not supported.
.PP
The escape sequences are not managed.
.PP
The addresses of the emulated peripherials are fixed. So the PILBox should be
placed immediately on OUT plug of the HP-IL controller.
.SH AUTHOR
The ilper was first developped by Jean-Francois Garnier under Windows/PC.
The port under Linux and *Nix platforms was done by Christophe Gottheimer.
